==English==
===Etymology===
An abbreviation of Yagi-Uda antenna. Named after two Japanese engineers Shintaro Uda and Hidetsugu Yagi.
===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A directional [[radio]] or [[TV]] [[antenna]] consisting of two or more [[dipole]]s in the same plane with all dipoles parallel to each other.

